<subSubSection lastPageId="4" pageId="2" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,835,860]" pageId="2">Description.</emphasis>
Morphometric data is presented at 
<tableCitation box="[759,846,836,861]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,1048,1071]" captionTargetBox="[159,1298,1098,1876]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphometric data for the holotype and paratypes of Melanorivulus nigropunctatus." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/4495CEEBFFE7FFB6FF7FC2134EA7143B" pageId="2" tableUuid="4495CEEBFFE7FFB6FF7FC2134EA7143B">Table 1</tableCitation>
. Males larger than females, largest male examined 
<quantity box="[151,254,872,896]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.41" pageId="2" unit="mm" value="24.1">24.1 mm</quantity>
SL, largest female 
<quantity box="[486,590,872,896]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.28" pageId="2" unit="mm" value="22.8">22.8 mm</quantity>
SL. Dorsal profile slightly convex from snout to end of dorsal-fin base, straight on caudal peduncle. Ventral profile weakly convex from lower jaw to origin of anal-fin, approximately straight to end of caudal peduncle. Body slender, approximately cylindrical and compressed, greatest body depth at midlength between pectoral-fin base and anal-fin base. Snout blunt. Jaws short.
</paragraph>
